  "steps": [
    {
      "title": "Cut Wood",
      "body": "Cut top shelf to 28 inches long and the two legs to 8 inches long, or according to the measurements for your particular cabinet.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/1ed0ac8b0085bee9.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Pocket Holes for Shelf",
      "body": "Using the Kreg jig pocket-hole jig, drill two holes on one of the legs, evenly spaced apart. Holes should follow the grain.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/a74ee58d8684861f.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Pocket Holes for Second Leg",
      "body": "Repeat for both legs.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/37def0e6e017a4a9.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Glue Edges",
      "body": "Glue the ends of the legs where the holes are and the ends of one of the faces of the top shelf.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/871b35dbea6bccd6.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Screw in Legs",
      "body": "Using Kreg jig screws attach legs to the top plate. Be sure the screw holes are faced towards the center of the shelf.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/0e71c986419111d2.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Prepare for final finish",
      "body": "Use Kreg Jig plugs and glue to fill in the screw holes then once dry, sand all surfaces flat and smooth.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/9e5998ee6df0a043.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Finish Wood",
      "body": "Apply paint or stain based on your preference. We used pickling stain with a polyurethane coat to lighten the color of the pine.\nIf you would like to see more of how we use these cabinet shelf risers to maximize storage in our RV, visit us at tidbits-cami.com.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/d880abdcb3812209.webp"
    }
  ],
